Title: Four Dimensional Yang - Mills Theory in Local Gauge Invariant Variables
Authors: F.A.Lunev
Comments: 13 pages, MSU-PHYS-HEP-Lu1/94
Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A9 (1994) 2281-2292
\\
  It is presented the general method that allows to formulate 4D $SU(N)$ Yang -
Mills theory in terms of only local gauge invariant variables. For the case
N=2, that is discussed in details, this gauge invariant formulation appears to
be very similar to $ R^2 $-gravity.
